---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Slides — SecID">
  <section>
    <h1>Presentations</h1>
    <p>Slide decks about SecID — what it is, how to use it, and how it integrates with CSA programs.</p>

    <div class="slides-grid">
      <div class="slide-card">
        <h2>SecID Overview</h2>
        <p class="slide-meta">19 slides · 10–15 minutes</p>
        <p>What SecID is, what v1.0 delivers (709+ namespaces, 10 types, 39 methodologies, 502 CNA partners), the tools ecosystem, and where v2.0 is headed. For executives, security practitioners, and anyone new to SecID.</p>
        <div class="slide-actions">
          <a href="/slides/overview.html" class="btn-primary" target="_blank">View Slides</a>
          <a href="https://github.com/CloudSecurityAlliance/SecID/raw/main/slides/secid-overview.pdf" class="btn-secondary">Download PDF</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="slide-card">
        <h2>SecID + CSA Integration</h2>
        <p class="slide-meta">14 slides · 10–15 minutes</p>
        <p>How SecID powers CCM, AICM, STAR, CCSK, and cross-framework mapping. Structured CNA data, methodology references, participation model. For CSA staff and members.</p>
        <div class="slide-actions">
          <a href="/slides/csa-integration.html" class="btn-primary" target="_blank">View Slides</a>
          <a href="https://github.com/CloudSecurityAlliance/SecID/raw/main/slides/secid-csa-integration.pdf" class="btn-secondary">Download PDF</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="slide-card">
        <h2>Technical Deep Dive</h2>
        <p class="slide-meta">15 slides · 15–20 minutes</p>
        <p>API contract, encoding gotcha, response envelope, MCP server, SDKs, self-hosted server, Claude Code plugin, building a client. For developers and integrators.</p>
        <div class="slide-actions">
          <a href="/slides/technical.html" class="btn-primary" target="_blank">View Slides</a>
          <a href="https://github.com/CloudSecurityAlliance/SecID/raw/main/slides/secid-technical.pdf" class="btn-secondary">Download PDF</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="slide-card">
        <h2>Contributing to SecID</h2>
        <p class="slide-meta">13 slides · 10–15 minutes</p>
        <p>Registry format, namespace algorithm, match_nodes, regex rules, research workflow, contribution process, participation model. For community contributors.</p>
        <div class="slide-actions">
          <a href="/slides/contributing.html" class="btn-primary" target="_blank">View Slides</a>
          <a href="https://github.com/CloudSecurityAlliance/SecID/raw/main/slides/secid-contributing.pdf" class="btn-secondary">Download PDF</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style is:global>
  .slides-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(340px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .slide-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: var(--surface);
    transition: border-color 0.15s;
  }

  .slide-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent);
  }

  .slide-card.upcoming {
    opacity: 0.6;
  }

  .slide-card h2 {
    margin: 0 0 0.25rem;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--fg);
  }

  .slide-meta {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .slide-card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
  }

  .slide-actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .btn-primary {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    background: var(--accent);
    color: #fff;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .btn-primary:hover {
    opacity: 0.9;
  }

  .btn-secondary {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--accent);
    color: var(--accent);
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .btn-secondary:hover {
    background: var(--accent);
    color: #fff;
  }
</style>
